A. What till now we have done:
- Code is written and structured
- Dependencies are managed (Poetry)
- Apps are containerized with Docker
- Code is version-controlled with Git
- CI pipelines run automatically using GitHub Actions
- Databases integrate with your backend
- Apps behave consistently across environments
✅ Multiple projects in one repo
✅ Separate environments
✅ Run both independently
✅ Clean professional setup

✅ Dockerized services
✅ Parallel test execution (Makefile)
✅ Testcontainers (DB isolation)
✅ CI pipeline
✅ Multi-service repo (myapp + mylearning)
✅ Basic CD (image push attempts)

B. Below Tag is created today, use to access the this state of repository whenever you want. 

git add -A
git commit -m "Checkpoint before refactor"
git tag -a refactor-start -m "Start of architecture refactor"
git push origin --tags
Later, you can go back to that exact commit:
git checkout refactor-start

C. Repo layout (Git + Helm + Argo‑ready)
Use this structure so it works both with plain Helm and Argo CD:
charts/
  myapp/
  mylearning/

environments/
  dev/
    values-myapp.yaml
    values-mylearning.yaml
  staging/
    values-myapp.yaml
    values-mylearning.yaml
  prod/
    values-myapp.yaml
    values-mylearning.yaml

infra/
  k8s/
    monitoring/
      namespace.yaml
      kube-prometheus-stack-values-dev.yaml
      kube-prometheus-stack-values-staging.yaml
      kube-prometheus-stack-values-prod.yaml
      grafana-dashboards-infra.yaml
      grafana-dashboards-myapp.yaml
    logging/
      namespace.yaml
      loki-stack-values-dev.yaml
      loki-stack-values-staging.yaml
      loki-stack-values-prod.yaml
    rules/
      prometheus-rules-base.yaml
      slo-rules-myapp.yaml

gitops/
  dev/
    argocd-app-monitoring.yaml
    argocd-app-logging.yaml
    argocd-app-myapp.yaml
  staging/
    argocd-app-monitoring.yaml
    argocd-app-logging.yaml
    argocd-app-myapp.yaml
  prod/
    argocd-app-monitoring.yaml
    argocd-app-logging.yaml
    argocd-app-myapp.yaml